# Google Cloud Storage Configuration
# ===================================
# Set these environment variables to use Google Cloud Storage

# Option 1: Use GCS (recommended for production)
USE_GCS=true
STORAGE_BACKEND=gcs

# Option 2: Use Replit Object Storage (development/testing)
# USE_GCS=false
# STORAGE_BACKEND=replit

# Google Cloud Project ID
GCS_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id

# GCS Bucket Name (create this bucket in your GCP project)
GCS_BUCKET_NAME=riddle-storage

# Path to your GCS service account key JSON file
# Download from: https://console.cloud.google.com/iam-admin/serviceaccounts
GCS_KEY_FILE=/path/to/your-service-account-key.json

# Alternative: Set GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS (GCP standard)
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/your-service-account-key.json

# ===================================
# Setup Instructions:
# ===================================
#
# 1. Create a GCP project: https://console.cloud.google.com
#
# 2. Enable Cloud Storage API:
#    https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/storage-api.googleapis.com
#
# 3. Create a storage bucket:
#    - Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/storage/browser
#    - Click "CREATE BUCKET"
#    - Name: riddle-storage (or your preferred name)
#    - Location: Choose closest to your users
#    - Storage class: Standard
#    - Access control: Fine-grained (IAM + ACLs)
#
# 4. Create a service account:
#    - Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/iam-admin/serviceaccounts
#    - Click "CREATE SERVICE ACCOUNT"
#    - Name: riddle-storage-service
#    - Role: Storage Admin (or Storage Object Admin for specific bucket)
#    - Click "CREATE KEY" > JSON
#    - Save the JSON file securely
#
# 5. Set environment variables:
#    - Add GCS_PROJECT_ID, GCS_BUCKET_NAME, GCS_KEY_FILE to your .env
#    - Or use GitHub Secrets for GitHub Codespaces
#
# 6. Bucket permissions (for public files):
#    - In GCP Console, go to your bucket
#    - Permissions tab > Grant Access
#    - Add "allUsers" with role "Storage Object Viewer" (for public read)
#
# ===================================
# Security Notes:
# ===================================
# - Never commit your service account key to git
# - Add *.json to .gitignore
# - Use IAM roles instead of ACLs when possible
# - Enable Cloud CDN for better performance
# - Set up lifecycle rules to auto-delete old files
# - Enable uniform bucket-level access for simplified permissions
